This transmits revised IRM 2.4.29, IDRS Terminal input, Command Codes TELEA, TELEC, TELED, and TELER for Telephone Processing.
2.4.29.1 Editorial changes were made to add internal controls.
IRM 2.4.29, dated January 1, 2010, is superseded.

) Program Goals: (

) Command Code TELER is used to research telephone numbers (including tensions, if applicable) present on the TIF. The request may be made for up eleven separate accounts. The HOME-TELEPHONE-NUMBER, the OTHER- TELEPHONE- NUMBER, CELL-TELEPHONE-NUMBER, and the INTL- TELEPHONE-NUMBER along with an Extension, if applicable will be displayed if present. The SOURCE-CD will also be displayed for each telephone number. There will be a separate response for each account number entered. See Exhibit
For Terminal Input/Output. (
) Command Code TELED is used to delete telephone number information on TIF. The request may be made for up to eleven separate accounts. See Exhibit
for Terminal Input/Output. (
) Command Code TELEA is used to establish telephone number information the TIF. The request may be made for up to ﬁve separate accounts. See Exhibit
for Terminal Input/Output. (
) Command Code TELEC is used to change telephone number information on the TIF. The request may be made for up to ﬁve separate accounts. See Exhibit
for Terminal Input/Output. (
) This IRM and the contained subsections provide the user the necessary infor- mation on how to use Command Codes TELED, TELEA, TELEC (
) Command Code TELER is used to research telephone numbers (including tensions, if applicable) present on the TIF (Taxpayer Information File) on the IDRS (Integrated Data Retrieval System) (
) The RCC(Research Command Code) Project Lead responsible for reviewing and implementing the Work Requests that affect TELER and for updating the contents of this IRM. Management (
) The Command Code TELER is managed by Work Requests which are submitted for changes and also by tickets which are submitted by users for corrections. (
) Access to this program is governed by SACS Processing
